1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,700
<i> Gio!</i>

2
00:00:01,700 --> 00:00:03,633
<i>Did Peter come to your
house earlier?</i>

3
00:00:03,633 --> 00:00:05,733
Are you really like that, or did
<i> you date us at the same time?</i>

4
00:00:05,733 --> 00:00:07,300
<i>I have a lot of things
I can't say.</i>

5
00:00:07,300 --> 00:00:09,267
<i> You can tell me now.</i>

6
00:00:09,267 --> 00:00:11,200
<i> I'll find out eventually.</i>

7
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:14,000
<i> I'd like to court you.
Is that okay?</i>

8
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:15,467
<i> Is there any way to stop you?</i>

9
00:00:16,300 --> 00:00:17,667
<i> Nope.</i>

10
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:22,067
<i>"Are you really not going
to show up anymore?"</i>

11
00:00:22,067 --> 00:00:23,667
"Answer my call!"

12
00:00:23,667 --> 00:00:25,100
<i> Who is this?</i>

13
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:26,300
<i>- This is all your fault!
- [GURGLING]</i>

14
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:28,433
<i> If you hadn't said anything,</i>

15
00:00:28,433 --> 00:00:31,300
<i>I wouldn't have been
beaten to the hotel!</i>

16
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,567
<i>What do you know
about the treasure?</i>

17
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:34,500
<i>I don't know what
you're talking about!</i>

18
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:35,567
<i> What if...</i>

19
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:37,733
<i>he overheard where
they were taking him,</i>

20
00:00:37,733 --> 00:00:39,800
so he marked the map right away?

21
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,500
<i> Right?</i>

22
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,400
<i> You have such
a big imagination, Cheska.</i>

23
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:47,100
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

24
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:48,267
Hey.

25
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:49,300
Stay close.

26
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:51,200
I think we're here.

27
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:54,500
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

28
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,100
Can you check the map again?

29
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:57,200
There.

30
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,400
Is it this?

31
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,733
I mean, that's what
the map says.

32
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:02,333
- [LEAVES RUSTLING]
- [SCREAMS] Aah!

33
00:01:02,333 --> 00:01:04,433
- Hey!
- What's wrong?!

34
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:05,767
Something moved over there!

35
00:01:05,767 --> 00:01:08,267
- [UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]
- What? Where?

36
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,633
I'll check if I got a picture.

37
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:12,767
- Did you get it?
- There's nothing!

38
00:01:12,767 --> 00:01:14,400
I don't think so! Gosh!

39
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:16,167
- Can we look?
- Can we please go home?

40
00:01:16,167 --> 00:01:18,367
Let's just go home, please.

41
00:01:18,367 --> 00:01:21,367
If Martin finds out we did this,
he'll get mad at me, please!

42
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,633
Remember when we went with Sari?

43
00:01:23,633 --> 00:01:25,333
This is worse than that!

44
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:26,500
Just don't tell him!

45
00:01:27,467 --> 00:01:29,100
We should go back.

46
00:01:30,467 --> 00:01:32,133
C'mon, we're already here!

47
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:33,800
We didn't see anything.

48
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,433
We've already proven that.

49
00:01:35,433 --> 00:01:37,333
So, you're saying that
that map is useless?

50
00:01:39,433 --> 00:01:41,533
- C'mon, please.
- Let's go.

51
00:01:41,567 --> 00:01:42,833
Let's go.

52
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:44,233
Be careful.

53
00:01:44,233 --> 00:01:46,467
- Fine.
- Follow me, okay?

54
00:01:46,467 --> 00:01:48,067
Hurry up. Watch your step.

55
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:55,500
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

56
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:51,133
[VITO] These are burner phones.

57
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:54,267
You won't be able to access
the entire phone,

58
00:02:54,267 --> 00:02:56,433
but you will
receive calls and texts.

59
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:59,200
So, it's useless.

60
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,900
This is better than nothing.

61
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:02,833
You can't take it
to the technician.

62
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:04,767
I know.

63
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:12,900
- [CELLPHONE RINGING]
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

64
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,467
[PHONE BEEPS]

65
00:03:25,467 --> 00:03:32,433
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

66
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:36,700
- [PHONE BEEPS]
- Well?

67
00:03:37,467 --> 00:03:39,700
No one's talking.

68
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:41,967
It's like they're waiting
for me to talk first.

69
00:03:41,967 --> 00:03:43,633
Don't do that.

70
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:46,400
[PHONE BEEPS]

71
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:51,433
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

72
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:55,367
<i> Speak to me, you bastard!</i>

73
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,733
[LEON] Do I reply?

74
00:03:57,433 --> 00:03:59,767
Yes, but only with
limited characters.

75
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:03,700
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

76
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:06,233
<i> Why don't you show yourself?</i>

77
00:04:10,233 --> 00:04:11,500
[CAR DOOR SLAMS]

78
00:04:16,300 --> 00:04:17,733
It was you.

79
00:04:19,567 --> 00:04:20,900
Which one, sir?

80
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:23,500
The one in the cemetery.

81
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,700
Ah...

82
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,200
Yes.

83
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:29,867
Why didn't you tell me?

84
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:33,000
Well, you never asked.

85
00:04:33,767 --> 00:04:35,800
Sir Ronald, however...

86
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,567
he asked.

87
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:39,533
Ah.

88
00:04:39,833 --> 00:04:41,233
Okay.

89
00:04:43,867 --> 00:04:45,733
Is that okay?

90
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:48,333
What's okay?

91
00:04:49,667 --> 00:04:50,967
The umbrella.

92
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,533
What you told Uncle Ronald?

93
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:56,767
No, not that.

94
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:00,567
I still have the umbrella.

95
00:05:01,900 --> 00:05:03,400
Ah.

96
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:06,800
No, it's fine.

97
00:05:08,033 --> 00:05:09,567
Keep it.

98
00:05:12,433 --> 00:05:14,000
Your seat belt.

99
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:19,633
[SEAT BELT CLATTERING]

100
00:05:19,633 --> 00:05:25,867
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

101
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:27,333
[SEAT BELT CLICKS]

102
00:05:35,733 --> 00:05:37,000
I'm good now.

103
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,500
Oh.

104
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,500
- I'm safe.
- Okay.

105
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:42,033
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

106
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:49,033
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

107
00:05:53,767 --> 00:05:58,500
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

108
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,700
[PHONE BEEPS]

109
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:04,867
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

110
00:06:04,867 --> 00:06:06,467
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

111
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:08,967
[PHONE BEEPS]

112
00:06:08,967 --> 00:06:13,967
<i>Tell me where the thing
I'm searching for is located</i>

113
00:06:15,133 --> 00:06:16,433
[PHONE BEEPS]

114
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:17,867
"Answer the call!"

115
00:06:17,867 --> 00:06:22,700
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

116
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:24,367
No matter what happens,

117
00:06:24,367 --> 00:06:26,600
never say a word.

118
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:33,567
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

119
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:46,833
- [MARTIN] Trixie?
- [KIKO] Cheska?

120
00:06:46,833 --> 00:06:48,000
Kiko! Hi

121
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,167
[MARTIN] Where have you been?

122
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:50,733
We just hung out.

123
00:06:52,067 --> 00:06:55,033
- [TRIXIE CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

124
00:06:55,033 --> 00:06:56,567
You were together, Trixie?

125
00:06:56,567 --> 00:06:57,900
Yes! Yes. Martin.

126
00:06:57,900 --> 00:07:00,100
We're actually...

127
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:03,633
we're busy talking about...
the bar!

128
00:07:03,633 --> 00:07:06,500
That's why we were
just hanging out on the beach.

129
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:09,133
You're always not around.

130
00:07:09,133 --> 00:07:11,667
Are you having a hard
time setting it up, Trixie?

131
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:14,000
- No! Absolutely not.
- I don't think so.

132
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:17,133
[CHUCKLES] I told you, Martin,
I got this.

133
00:07:17,167 --> 00:07:18,833
- We can do this, right?
- Yeah!

134
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:20,733
And Martin, Kiko...

135
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:23,167
I'm gonna be managing her bar.

136
00:07:23,167 --> 00:07:25,833
We can do this, I'll handle it!

137
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:28,700
Just do it right, so your boss
won't have a hard time.

138
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,100
I am doing it right!

139
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:32,600
Aren't I, boss?
I'm helping her out!

140
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:35,967
That's why I'll start
unwinding my boss.

141
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:39,033
- We'll leave now.
- Yes, bye!

142
00:07:39,033 --> 00:07:41,733
- This might go all night. Bye!
- Yeah, you're right.

143
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:48,733
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

144
00:07:48,767 --> 00:07:50,100
What?

145
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,867
What? What's this?

146
00:07:53,867 --> 00:07:55,567
- Did you order something?
- Huh?

147
00:07:55,567 --> 00:07:58,200
Why would I order?
There's a lot of food here.

148
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:00,700
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:03,000
Who is this from?

150
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:07,000
"To make sure you
don't go hungry. - Edward"

151
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:11,900
It's from... Edward.

152
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:14,867
Look at that!

153
00:08:14,867 --> 00:08:17,100
Wait, I'll call him.

154
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:18,167
Okay.

155
00:08:19,533 --> 00:08:20,867
Ma'am is so pretty.

156
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:22,233
Look at all these!

157
00:08:22,233 --> 00:08:24,200
Hey! Wow!

158
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,133
What is this? Is this all free?

159
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:27,933
Yes, it's from the supplier.

160
00:08:28,667 --> 00:08:29,967
Wow.

161
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:32,233
[INDISTINCT MUMBLING]

162
00:08:32,233 --> 00:08:34,700
- Mmmh!
- Hey! That's not yours!

163
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,700
- What's wrong?
- That's from the supplier!

164
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,933
- Am I not allowed to eat it?
- Ms. Jade's happiness supplier.

165
00:08:38,933 --> 00:08:40,500
It's from Sir Edward.

166
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,233
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

167
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:45,567
- [JADE] Um, thanks for the...
- How could I beat that?

168
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:47,200
- food you gave.
- What did you say?

169
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,000
Nothing. Well, alright.
I'll go there now.

170
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,533
It doesn't taste good.

171
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:53,567
Huh? But he still
took the<i> siopao</i> .

172
00:08:56,700 --> 00:08:59,000
Sir Edward is so sweet!

173
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,600
Oh! That stinks!

174
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:04,100
What is that?!

175
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:08,300
[FAUCET CREAKS]

176
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,767
The water always runs out
at this hour.

177
00:09:12,633 --> 00:09:15,533
[FAUCET CREAKS]

178
00:09:15,533 --> 00:09:22,933
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

179
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:31,000
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

180
00:09:35,233 --> 00:09:39,133
[METAL WHEEL CREAKS]

181
00:09:39,133 --> 00:09:46,167
[WATER RUNNING]

182
00:09:46,167 --> 00:09:53,100
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:07,067
[ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:28,067
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

185
00:10:28,067 --> 00:10:30,367
[PHOTOGRAPHER] Good!
Just keep doing that.

186
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:32,767
Uh...

187
00:10:33,367 --> 00:10:34,967
Uh, err...

188
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:37,933
Uh... I think they get it now.

189
00:10:37,933 --> 00:10:44,867
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

190
00:10:47,967 --> 00:10:49,233
[EDWARD CLEARS THROAT]

191
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:50,400
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

192
00:10:54,967 --> 00:10:56,200
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

193
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:59,300
Bro, thank you for the free
photo shoot.

194
00:10:59,300 --> 00:11:01,500
It's not included
in the hotel's package

195
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,367
but you gave it
to us regardless.

196
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:06,867
All good, sir. We'll both
benefit from it anyway.

197
00:11:06,867 --> 00:11:08,467
This also counts
as the hotel's promotion.

198
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:09,833
[CHUCKLES]

199
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,467
You two really suit each other.

200
00:11:14,233 --> 00:11:15,133
Pardon?

201
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:17,533
I said, you two
look good together.

202
00:11:17,533 --> 00:11:19,900
Your chemistry together
is off the chart!

203
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:21,900
To think that you're only
standing in.

204
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:23,167
Are you going out?

205
00:11:24,333 --> 00:11:25,367
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

206
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:27,900
Not yet.

207
00:11:28,533 --> 00:11:29,967
But we will be soon.

208
00:11:30,233 --> 00:11:32,367
Oh, so you're courting her?

209
00:11:36,567 --> 00:11:38,133
Yes.

210
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:44,000
And when she says yes
I'll be the happiest man alive.

211
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:50,933
[ROMANTIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:02,833
It really does look different
from how it looked before.

213
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:04,367
Good or bad?

214
00:12:05,267 --> 00:12:07,533
Hmm, let's just say uh...

215
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:11,367
Michael did a great job
in renovating the place.

216
00:12:11,833 --> 00:12:13,233
Actually, the same goes
for you guys.

217
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:15,200
Your management
is also excellent.

218
00:12:15,233 --> 00:12:18,233
Of course there are...
unforeseen circumstances

219
00:12:18,233 --> 00:12:19,867
but, nothing you can do
about it.

220
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,600
So Luna, about the bank notice,

221
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,567
you don't have to worry
about it anymore, hm?

222
00:12:25,567 --> 00:12:26,833
I talked to the bank already

223
00:12:26,833 --> 00:12:29,000
and you don't have to worry
about the payment.

224
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,367
Uncle, are you serious?

225
00:12:30,367 --> 00:12:32,133
I am, but...

226
00:12:32,633 --> 00:12:34,100
It's not for free.

227
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:37,233
Of course, Uncle.

228
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,867
This is still a business
after all.

229
00:12:39,867 --> 00:12:42,167
And I assure you,
everything you invest in

230
00:12:42,167 --> 00:12:43,233
will have an ROI.

231
00:12:44,033 --> 00:12:45,300
I'm not worried.

232
00:12:45,533 --> 00:12:47,400
I know I won't lose out
with you guys.

233
00:12:48,367 --> 00:12:51,633
Besides, now that I see
Edward enjoying,

234
00:12:53,167 --> 00:12:55,867
I'm sure I invested
in the right thing.

235
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:00,000
Anyway, if you need
anything else,

236
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,600
don't hesitate to ask, okay?

237
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,000
[LUNA] Thank you, Uncle.

238
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,400
- I'll get going, Luna.
- Thank you.

239
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,667
Take care.

240
00:13:05,667 --> 00:13:12,600
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

241
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:30,400
[PENCIL SCRIBBLING]

242
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:32,633
[PAPER RUSTLING]

243
00:13:33,233 --> 00:13:40,167
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

244
00:13:42,533 --> 00:13:43,667
[RAPHIE CLEARS THROAT]

245
00:13:43,667 --> 00:13:45,933
Those gazes are intense,
Ms. Jade.

246
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,667
You know, Edward
really just has a way

247
00:13:48,667 --> 00:13:53,000
for me to forget about
my feelings for Kiko.

248
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:55,000
- Hmm...
- But...

249
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:56,967
maybe it's for the best, Raphie.

250
00:13:57,533 --> 00:14:01,133
For us to... remain
as best friends.

251
00:14:01,467 --> 00:14:02,700
Mm...

252
00:14:03,667 --> 00:14:06,100
He isn't just...
a rebound, right?

253
00:14:08,067 --> 00:14:09,533
I don't think so.

254
00:14:10,467 --> 00:14:13,467
'Cause... Kiko and I
never got together anyway.

255
00:14:13,467 --> 00:14:15,267
- Mm-hmm.
- Plus, I feel like

256
00:14:15,267 --> 00:14:17,433
it has a low chance
of happening.

257
00:14:19,167 --> 00:14:21,200
Okay. If you say so.

258
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,100
Well I also think that...

259
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,100
It's finally time for me
to open up my heart

260
00:14:29,133 --> 00:14:31,367
to someone who's willing
to bet on me.

261
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,100
To be on you, huh?!

262
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:37,033
- Aren't you fierce!
- Ow! Hm.

263
00:14:37,033 --> 00:14:39,033
I support you, Ms. Jade.

264
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:41,500
But, I just have one question.

265
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,700
Will you actually learn
how to love him?

266
00:14:49,633 --> 00:14:51,300
I think so.

267
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:55,500
I used to like him before
anyway.

268
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:58,567
You know when we were
in high school,

269
00:14:58,567 --> 00:15:01,300
he was so cute
because he was so chubby.

270
00:15:03,533 --> 00:15:04,633
That's why...

271
00:15:04,633 --> 00:15:06,533
I feel like I won't have
a hard time

272
00:15:06,533 --> 00:15:09,533
looking for things
to love about him.

273
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,533
How ferocious!

274
00:15:11,533 --> 00:15:13,367
He already checks off one box.

275
00:15:13,367 --> 00:15:15,000
He's generous.

276
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:17,367
You think more on generous?

277
00:15:17,367 --> 00:15:20,433
Oh for me,
he's immediately a yes!

278
00:15:20,667 --> 00:15:22,600
And we're just at one box.

279
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:25,067
What more for the other boxes.

280
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:27,767
[BOTH GIGGLING]

281
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:31,633
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

282
00:15:31,633 --> 00:15:38,600
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

283
00:15:47,767 --> 00:15:50,500
- [CLICKS TONGUE] Luna--
- What do you want, Peter?!

284
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,233
What did I do wrong this time?!

285
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:54,300
You know what I mean.

286
00:15:54,633 --> 00:15:57,367
Luna, I am my own person.

287
00:15:57,367 --> 00:15:59,533
I can do whatever I want to do.

288
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,400
This is a hotel.

289
00:16:01,767 --> 00:16:03,467
You're in business.

290
00:16:03,467 --> 00:16:04,700
I am a customer.

291
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:07,400
What? Are you gonna kick me out?

292
00:16:10,367 --> 00:16:12,267
- Luna!
- Let go of me!

293
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:14,233
What do you want?!

294
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:16,133
I just want to talk to you!

295
00:16:16,567 --> 00:16:18,400
It's been over for us
for a while now, Peter.

296
00:16:20,633 --> 00:16:21,567
[LUNA] Enough.

297
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:23,400
- [PETER] Luna!
- [LUNA] Leave me alone!

298
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:25,300
[PETER] Luna!

299
00:16:25,300 --> 00:16:32,267
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

300
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,800
[LUNA] Let go of me!

301
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,800
Let go of me! I don't want
to come with you!

302
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:43,633
I just want to talk to you!

303
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:46,233
Then let's talk here!

304
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:48,767
You know me, Luna.

305
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:51,467
I don't care if others
get involved.

306
00:16:51,467 --> 00:16:52,833
Do you remember that day?

307
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:54,367
An innocent person got involved.

308
00:16:54,367 --> 00:16:55,867
And that's all because of you!

309
00:16:56,367 --> 00:16:58,633
- It your fault someone died--
- Alright! Alright!

310
00:16:58,633 --> 00:16:59,800
I'll go.

311
00:16:59,800 --> 00:17:01,333
Get a move on!

312
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:04,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

313
00:17:04,567 --> 00:17:06,300
Luna, you're not going anywhere.

314
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:07,667
Mind your business!

315
00:17:07,667 --> 00:17:08,867
You think I'm scared of you?

316
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:15,267
Then maybe this will.

317
00:17:16,167 --> 00:17:19,100
[LUNA CRYING] Don't!
Don't shoot!

318
00:17:20,233 --> 00:17:22,733
[LUNA] Peter! Don't!

319
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:26,167
Peter, put that down.
I'll go with you!

320
00:17:26,167 --> 00:17:29,133
Peter, put it away!
I'll come with you!

321
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:30,933
[LUNA WHIMPERING]

322
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:37,133
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

323
00:17:37,133 --> 00:17:39,333
Luna, let's go!

324
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:45,633
Put the gun down already!

325
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:47,067
Hurry!

326
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:55,067
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [LUNA SCREAMS]

327
00:17:55,067 --> 00:17:56,800
- [PETER GRUNTING]
- [LUNA] Gio!

328
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,633
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [INAUDIBLE]

329
00:17:58,633 --> 00:17:59,867
[LUNA SCREAMS]

330
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:02,233
- [BLOW LANDS]
- Stop it! Please!

331
00:18:02,233 --> 00:18:04,700
- [PETER SCREAMING]
- Stop it, Peter!

332
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:05,733
[THUDS]

333
00:18:05,733 --> 00:18:08,733
- [BLOW LANDS]
- That's enough!

334
00:18:11,867 --> 00:18:13,733
Stop it! Stop it!

335
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:17,067
[BLOWS LANDING]

336
00:18:17,067 --> 00:18:18,833
- [PETER GRUNTING IN PAIN]
- [GIO GRUNTING]

337
00:18:18,833 --> 00:18:20,400
[STUTTERING] Security...
Security!

338
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,800
Go here at the docks!
Sir Gio and a guest--

339
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:25,000
Hey! Get over here quick!

340
00:18:25,233 --> 00:18:26,667
[PHONE BEEPS]

341
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:27,967
Sir Martin!

342
00:18:27,967 --> 00:18:30,433
- [BLOW LANDS]
- [PETER GRUNTS]

343
00:18:30,433 --> 00:18:31,800
- [KICK LANDS]
- [GIO GROANS]

344
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:34,667
[LUNA SCREAMING] Stop it,
Peter, Gio!

345
00:18:34,667 --> 00:18:35,800
[THUDS LOUDLY]

346
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,267
- [BLOWS LANDING]
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

347
00:18:39,067 --> 00:18:40,233
- [SMACK LANDS]
- Ack!

348
00:18:40,233 --> 00:18:44,667
- [GRASS CRUNCHING]
- [BOTH GRUNTING]

349
00:18:44,667 --> 00:18:47,333
Please, stop it already!

350
00:18:48,933 --> 00:18:50,367
[MARTIN] Hey! Stop it!

351
00:18:50,367 --> 00:18:51,600
Security, break them off!

352
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:54,433
- Sir, that's enough.
- Sir, stop fighting.

353
00:18:54,433 --> 00:18:55,900
Sir, calm down.

354
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:57,867
- Let go of me!
- [MARTIN] Stop it!

355
00:18:57,867 --> 00:18:59,267
-[MARTIN] Kiko, call the police!
- [LUNA] Peter!

356
00:18:59,967 --> 00:19:01,900
Call them!
Call the police, Kiko!

357
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:02,767
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Gio, calm down!

358
00:19:02,767 --> 00:19:04,900
Go ahead and try calling
the police!

359
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:06,933
I'll kill all of you!

360
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:10,433
[PHONE RINGING CONTINUES]

361
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:12,833
Security, after him!

362
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:18,367
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

363
00:19:18,367 --> 00:19:19,833
Luna...

364
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:27,833
[LUNA BREATHING HEAVILY]

365
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:31,233
- Luna! Luna!
- [LUNA WAILING]

366
00:19:31,267 --> 00:19:32,767
- Raphie, get some water!
- O-- okay.

367
00:19:32,767 --> 00:19:34,300
- Anything, hurry!
- Yes, sir!

368
00:19:36,033 --> 00:19:38,200
Luna, calm down.

369
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:41,100
Luna... Luna, I'm here.

370
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,033
Luna.

371
00:19:44,067 --> 00:19:46,167
Luna, look at me. Luna.

372
00:19:48,933 --> 00:19:55,733
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

373
00:19:55,733 --> 00:19:56,733
Security!

374
00:19:57,133 --> 00:19:58,200
Go that way.

375
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:00,233
Let's meet back at the hotel!
Move!

376
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:07,800
This wouldn't have happened!

377
00:20:08,933 --> 00:20:11,800
It's all my fault!
It's all my fault!

378
00:20:12,467 --> 00:20:14,967
- It's all because of me!
- Luna, Luna!

379
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:17,433
Luna, relax.

380
00:20:17,933 --> 00:20:19,100
Luna, please look at me.

381
00:20:19,100 --> 00:20:22,367
- Luna!
- It's all my fault!

382
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:25,067
- [WAILING, SNIFFLING]

383
00:20:25,067 --> 00:20:26,967
[JADE] Luna! Luna!

384
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:28,833
- Luna, what happened?
- Luna!

385
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:31,900
- Luna, just breathe.
- I'm here.

386
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:33,200
No!

387
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,067
- Luna, what happened?
- It's all my fault!

388
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:37,167
Luna, no it's not!

389
00:20:37,167 --> 00:20:38,400
Water, please!

390
00:20:39,067 --> 00:20:42,300
- Water!
- [JADE] Luna, just breathe.

391
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:44,367
- Luna, calm down.
- I'm here.

392
00:20:44,367 --> 00:20:46,967
Jade, it's all my fault!

393
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:48,800
Luna, breathe!

394
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:49,933
- Gio, what happened?!
- [LUNA WHIMPERS]

395
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:51,567
- Luna!
- Luna.

396
00:20:51,567 --> 00:20:55,833
[LUNA WAILING CONTINUES]

397
00:20:56,767 --> 00:20:57,467
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

398
00:20:57,467 --> 00:21:04,300
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

399
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:26,333
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

400
00:21:29,433 --> 00:21:30,400
What is this?

401
00:21:37,633 --> 00:21:39,333
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

402
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:51,600
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

403
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:13,533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

404
00:22:16,067 --> 00:22:19,100
[BATS CHIRPING]

405
00:22:26,467 --> 00:22:28,133
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

406
00:22:28,133 --> 00:22:35,100
[MUSIC TURNS EERIE]

407
00:22:49,867 --> 00:22:51,200
- [MAN] Who are you?!
- [PETER SCREAMS]

408
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,200
[BODY THUDS]

409
00:22:56,067 --> 00:23:01,867
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

410
00:23:03,867 --> 00:23:04,900
[WATER POURS]

411
00:23:04,900 --> 00:23:07,533
<i> Peter is missing at Hotel 88.</i>

412
00:23:07,533 --> 00:23:08,767
<i> That's where he was last seen.</i>

413
00:23:08,767 --> 00:23:11,000
Someone else is also interested
<i> in your hotel, Martin.</i>

414
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,067
<i> Is there a problem?</i>

415
00:23:12,067 --> 00:23:15,133
<i>I won't enter this venture
if he's involved.</i>

416
00:23:15,133 --> 00:23:17,467
It's either me or Andy Arellano.

417
00:23:17,467 --> 00:23:19,800
<i>Luna will get hurt if we go
against them again.</i>

418
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:22,467
<i>Why is that?
No matter what we do,</i>

419
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:25,833
the past always finds a way to
come back into our lives today.

420
00:23:25,833 --> 00:23:28,867
<i>It can never be escaped
anymore.</i>

421
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:30,800
<i>I'm not happy
with your game anymore.</i>
